<section xml:id="D4" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>D4: Sketching the Derivative</title>
    <objectives>
        <dl>
            <li>
                <title>D4</title>
                <p>
                    Given a graph, I can sketch its derivative.
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </objectives>

    <subsection xml:id="D4-activities">
        <title>In-Class Activities</title>

        <activity xml:id="d-activity-sketch-1">
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Let <m>f(x) = 2x-x^2</m>.
                </p>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Compute <m>f'(x)</m>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
            <task>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Use the <c>Calc</c> tool at the top of the page to graph <m>f(x)</m> and <m>f'(x)</m>. Which relationship(s) do you observe to be true?
                        <ol marker="A." cols="2">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    When the function is increasing, the derivative graph is positive
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    When the function is decreasing, the derivative graph is negative
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    When the function is not changing, the derivative graph is zero
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    There is no connection between the graph of <m>f(x)</m> and <m>f'(x)</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </task>
        </activity>

